  "prompt": "What are cars of tata?",
  "response": "Tata Motors, an Indian multinational automotive manufacturing company, produces a wide range of vehicles, including passenger cars, trucks, vans, buses, and military vehicles. As of my last update in October 2023, here are some of the passenger cars produced by Tata Motors:\n\n### 1. **Hatchbacks:**\n   - **Tata Tiago:** A compact hatchback known for its stylish design, features, and fuel efficiency.\n   - **Tata Altroz:** A premium hatchback built on the ALFA (Agile Light Flexible Advanced) architecture, offering a premium feel and safety features.\n\n### 2. **Sedans:**\n   - **Tata Tigor:** A compact sedan based on the Tiago platform, offering a blend of style and practicality.\n   - **Tata Tigor EV:** An electric version of the Tigor, catering to the growing demand for eco-friendly vehicles.\n   - **Tata Zest:** Previously a popular compact sedan, though it has been discontinued in some markets.\n\n### 3. **SUVs:**\n   - **Tata Nexon:** A compact SUV known for its bold design, safety features (5-star Global NCAP rating), and both petrol and diesel engine options.\n   - **Tata Nexon EV:** An electric version of the Nexon, offering a long range and advanced features.\n   - **Tata Harrier:** A mid-size SUV with a rugged design, premium interiors, and powerful performance, based on the OMEGA ARC platform derived from Land Rover's D8 architecture.\n   - **Tata Safari:** A full-size SUV with three-row seating, offering a luxurious and spacious interior, essentially a three-row version of the Harrier.\n   - **Tata Punch:** A micro-SUV designed for urban driving, offering a compact yet robust design and features typically found in larger SUVs.\n\n### 4. **Electric Vehicles (EVs):**\n   - **Tata Nexon EV:** One of the best-selling electric SUVs in India, offering a range of around 300-400 km on a single charge.\n   - **Tata Tigor EV:** An electric compact sedan, ideal for urban commuting.\n   - **Tata Tiago EV:** An electric version of the popular Tiago hatchback, aimed at the budget electric vehicle segment.\n\n### 5. **Concept Cars:**\n   - **Tata Sierra EV:** A futuristic electric SUV concept that revives the iconic Sierra nameplate, showcasing Tata Motors' vision for electric mobility.\n   - **Tata Avinya:** A concept electric vehicle that represents Tata Motors' commitment to sustainable and advanced mobility solutions.\n\n### 6. **Upcoming Models:**\n   - Tata Motors is continuously working on new models and updates to existing ones, including more electric vehicles (EVs) and advanced technologies in their lineup.\n\nTata Motors has been focusing on enhancing its portfolio with vehicles that emphasize safety, design, technology, and sustainability, particularly in the electric vehicle segment.",
